						<summary>

						<p>On the north wall, central shrine, Nāgēśvarasvāmi temple.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">Year 8, Kumbha, Thursday, Aviṭṭam = 30th January 979 A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>Damaged. Seems to register a gift of 96 sheep for a perpetual lamp to God Paramasvāmin of Tirukkīḻkōṭṭam at Tirukkuḍamukkil, a <hi rend="italic">dēvadāṉam</hi> of Pāmbūr-nāḍu by Pichchaṉ, a member of the regiment <hi rend="italic">(Gaṇḍarādittatt-teriñja-kaikkōḷar ?)</hi></p>						

						<p>Published in <hi rend="italic">S.I.I.,</hi> Vol. III. No. 131.</p>						

						</summary>
